AeroScan v0.2c
NEW: Radar Scope reworked as a classic phosphor
P-scope — glowing sweep with decay trail, tube
glow, range rings, cardinal ticks, ownship
cross, and a fixed 240px sweep radius. GPS
readout (top right) now shows ground speed and
MSL altitude — an altitude bug affecting
GPS-only receivers (u-blox 7) is fixed. Remote
SDR server: stream a dongle to SDR++/GQRX/SDR#
from Settings > Radio Options. Map and radar
scopes now render aircraft identically.

APPLIANCE: the GUI restarts itself after any
crash, the power menu now really powers off /
reboots, a hardware watchdog recovers kernel
hangs, and logs/screenshots are size-capped —
built to run indefinitely.

RF: interference was traced to the display
panel. Remoting the SDR receiver on a USB
extension fixed it — verified 1800+ msg/min.
